      "identifier": "action-contract-source-of-truth-split",
      "summary": "The upload action surface is tested against replicated expectations in multiple files instead of one explicit ownership point.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/protocol/actions/actions.go",
        "goseg/uploadsvc/adapters/upload_payload_test.go",
        "goseg/uploadsvc/service_test.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "Protocol exposes action lists and metadata via `SupportedActions/UploadActionContracts`, while adapter and service tests each build their own assertions over action behavior and dispatch expectations",
        "Any new action addition requires updating protocol metadata plus separate, manually maintained test assumptions in adapter/service tests rather than consuming one canonical contract"
      ],
      "suggestion": "Introduce one canonical upload action contract artifact (single exported slice or generated contract type) that both parser/dispatcher and tests consume, and derive expected behavior tables directly from it.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "architectural_change",
      "root_cause_cluster": "action_contract_schema_fragmentation"
    }
  ],
  "retrospective": {
    "root_causes": [
      "Action contract ownership is fragmented across protocol metadata and service-level tests, creating duplicated interpretation of action semantics.",
      "Current contract shape relies on orthogonal booleans rather than a constrained schema, allowing invalid combinations and coupling to spread through call sites."
    ],
    "likely_symptoms": [
      "action_contract_schema_fragmentation"
    ],
    "possible_false_positives": []
